In this week's cartoon by Carlos, Egyptian President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi prepares for a long reign, with the help of a tame national parliament that has voted to amend the constitution to allow him to rule until 2030. Citizens can block the move in referendum currently under way – but with state repression increasing and democratic freedoms in tatters, el-Sisi has a good chance of winning that vote too. The 2011 Tahrir Square revolution has been tragically betrayed. You might be interested in: 
